# NUF Scoring Matrix

## NUF Criteria

| Criterion | Question |
|-----------|----------|
| New | Is the idea different or improved compared with current alternatives? |
| Useful | Does it solve a meaningful problem for a clear user? |
| Feasible | Can the team prototype it within the semester using available skills and tools? |

## Scoring Scale

| Score | Meaning |
|---------|----------|
| 1 | Very Weak |
| 2 | Weak |
| 3 | Moderate |
| 4 | Strong |
| 5 | Very Strong |

## Opportunity Scoring

| Idea | New | Useful | Feasible | Total | Rank | Notes |
|------|-----|--------|----------|-------|------|-------|
| Student Project Management System | 5 | 5 | 5 | 15 | 1 | Selected MVP |
| Student Attendance Reminder System | 4 | 4 | 5 | 13 | 2 | Good Alternative |
| Campus Service Information System | 3 | 4 | 5 | 12 | 3 | Feasible |
| Event Management Platform | 3 | 3 | 4 | 10 | 4 | Moderate |
| Team Progress Dashboard | 4 | 3 | 4 | 11 | 5 | Moderate |
| Meeting Scheduler System | 3 | 3 | 4 | 10 | 6 | Optional |

## Formula

Total Score:

=SUM(B2:D2)

Ranking Formula:

=RANK(E2,$E$2:$E$7,0)

## Final Selection

The Student Project Management System received the highest NUF score (15/15) and was selected as the semester MVP project because it is new, useful, and highly feasible for development within the available semester timeline.
